<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[136,1451,1958,2093]" lastBlockId="31.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis box="[136,245,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Perennial</emphasis>
, caulescent, stem well-developed (
<quantity box="[643,742,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="23.5" valueMax="46.0" valueMin="1.0">1–46 cm</quantity>
in length) with distinct internodes. Active growing 
<emphasis box="[1331,1401,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">leaves</emphasis>
few to numerous (3–13), with circinate vernation, petiole linear, 2–3 times narrower than the lamina, lamina lanceolate; stipules triangular to narrowly triangular, divided into few to several laciniae on the apical 1/2–1/3, golden-brown, often with paler margins. Dense indumentum of long white eglandular trichomes and TSG trichomes on leaves, scapes, pedicels and sepals. 
<emphasis box="[369,439,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Petals</emphasis>
obovate to broadly obovate, overlapping in anthesis, pink; gynoecium 3-carpelate, styles bifurcated at the base. 
<emphasis box="[389,453,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Seeds</emphasis>
oblong, testa reticulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,266,292]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M." box="[321,644,266,292]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="75 - 105" refId="ref59136" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M. (1997) Levantamento das Droseraceae do Brasil. Boletim de Botanica da Universidade de Sao Paulo 16: 75 - 105." type="journal article" year="1997">
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[321,377,266,292]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
&amp; Giulietti (1997: 101
</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 13A, C–M—habit and details); Rivadavia (2003: 86, figs. 3.2A– F—habit and details).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,338,364]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<collectingCountry box="[374,442,338,364]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Northeast: BA; Southeast: MG), endemic. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[989,1225,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[989,1225,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Drosera chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a patchy distribution in the 
<emphasis box="[346,543,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">campos rupestres</emphasis>
of the Espinhaço Range, from the municipality of Caeté (central 
<collectingRegion box="[1291,1444,374,400]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
) to the Chapada Diamantina (in 
<collectingRegion box="[485,554,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bahia</collectingRegion>
), and disjunctly on coastal sandy plains (
<emphasis box="[1012,1114,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
) in central coastal 
<collectingRegion box="[1326,1391,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(Fig. 7a).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,291,482,508]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Habitat:</emphasis>
—In the Espinhaço Range 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[596,760,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[596,760,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in wet areas of 
<emphasis box="[1042,1217,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">campo rupestre</emphasis>
vegetation on sandy to sandy peat soils, or in drier areas on sandy soil with white quartz gravel, at elevations around 
<quantity box="[1208,1366,518,545]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="1500.0" valueMax="1800.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–1800 m</quantity>
. On the coastal 
<emphasis box="[221,323,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
it is found just a few meters above sea level on wet sandy flats.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,590,616]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Phenology:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[351,577,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[351,577,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Drosera chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces flowers from April to September, corresponding to the end of the wet season and middle of the dry season.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,442,662,688]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—Near Threatened (NT). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[753,987,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[753,987,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Drosera chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed though relatively localized within its range, usually in small populations restricted to very specific and fragile habitats. The calculated EOO (
<quantity box="[212,351,734,761]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.52109" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="252109.0">252,109 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[351,359,734,748]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
) would place it in the LC category, however, the AOO (
<quantity box="[1025,1115,734,760]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.72" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="172.0">172 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1114,1122,734,748]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
) suggests EN. Although the species does not currently qualify for a category of threat, an observed reduction in area of occupancy due to mining, agriculture, cattle ranching, invasive grasses, and climate change in its 
<emphasis box="[951,1148,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">campos rupestres</emphasis>
range, as well as to urban expansion in its 
<emphasis box="[320,411,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restinga</emphasis>
range, all suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[671,833,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[671,833,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may likely qualify in the near future. It is found inside National Parks (Chapada Diamantina and Serra do Cipó, in BA and MG respectively) and State Parks (Rio Preto and Serra Nova, in MG), among other smaller locally protected areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,950,976]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[294,522,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[294,522,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Drosera chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rivadavia" authorityYear="2003" box="[734,943,951,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camporupestris">
<emphasis box="[734,943,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. camporupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by characters discussed under that species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Previous records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[417,580,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[417,580,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[649,742,1022,1048]" name="Ecuador" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[799,850,1023,1049]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Correa A. &amp; Silva, T. R. S." box="[865,1105,1022,1049]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref53788" refString="Correa A., M. D. &amp; Silva, T. R. S. (2005) Drosera (Droseraceae). Flora Neotropica Monograph 96. The New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 65 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Correa &amp; 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[981,1039,1022,1048]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
; assigned as possibly being 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rivadavia" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camporupestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. camporupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Rivadavia 2003), turned out to be a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella et al. (2016: 1421)" authorityName="Gonella et al. (2016:" authorityPageNumber="1421" authorityYear="1421" box="[936,1360,1058,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="condor">
<emphasis box="[936,1049,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. condor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gonella, P. M. &amp; Fleischmann, A. &amp; Rivadavia, F. &amp; Neill, D. A. &amp; Sano, P. T." box="[1056,1360,1058,1084]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1419 - 1432" refId="ref55906" refString="Gonella, P. M., Fleischmann, A., Rivadavia, F., Neill, D. A. &amp; Sano, P. T. (2016) A revision of Drosera (Droseraceae) from central and northern Andes, including a new species from the Cordillera del Condor (Peru and Ecuador). Plant Systematics and Evolution 302: 1419 - 1432. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 016 - 1341 - 3" type="journal article" year="2016">
Gonella 
<emphasis box="[1151,1207,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 1421)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, closely related to the Venezuelan 
<taxonomicName authority="Tamayo &amp; Croizat (1949: 175)" authorityName="Tamayo &amp; Croizat" authorityPageNumber="175" authorityYear="1949" box="[424,932,1094,1121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cendeensis">
<emphasis box="[424,579,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. cendeensis</emphasis>
Tamayo &amp; Croizat (1949: 175)
</taxonomicName>
and the Peruvian 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Correa (2002: 543)" authorityName="Silva &amp; Correa" authorityPageNumber="543" authorityYear="2002" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peruensis">
<emphasis box="[1134,1275,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. peruensis</emphasis>
Silva &amp; Correa (2002: 543)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gonella, P. M. &amp; Fleischmann, A. &amp; Rivadavia, F. &amp; Neill, D. A. &amp; Sano, P. T." box="[282,503,1130,1156]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1419 - 1432" refId="ref55906" refString="Gonella, P. M., Fleischmann, A., Rivadavia, F., Neill, D. A. &amp; Sano, P. T. (2016) A revision of Drosera (Droseraceae) from central and northern Andes, including a new species from the Cordillera del Condor (Peru and Ecuador). Plant Systematics and Evolution 302: 1419 - 1432. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 016 - 1341 - 3" type="journal article" year="2016">
Gonella 
<emphasis box="[379,436,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taubert" authorityYear="1893" box="[189,418,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysolepis">
<emphasis box="[189,418,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Drosera chrysolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Taubert, P. H. W." box="[631,799,1166,1192]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="502 - 506" refId="ref59347" refString="Taubert, P. H. W. (1893) Plantae Glaziovianae novae vel minus cognitae. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 17: 502 - 506." type="journal article" year="1893">Taubert (1893)</bibRefCitation>
based on the specimen 
<emphasis box="[1074,1241,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Glaziou 18857</emphasis>
from the Serra do Cipó, but the author did not cite the herbarium where this material was examined, which makes all known duplicates of this specimen 
<typeStatus box="[325,427,1239,1265]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M." box="[437,704,1238,1264]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="75 - 105" refId="ref59136" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M. (1997) Levantamento das Droseraceae do Brasil. Boletim de Botanica da Universidade de Sao Paulo 16: 75 - 105." type="journal article" year="1997">
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,495,1238,1264]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
&amp; Giulietti (1997)
</bibRefCitation>
cite the specimen deposited at K as an isotype, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Correa A. &amp; Silva, T. R. S." pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref53788" refString="Correa A., M. D. &amp; Silva, T. R. S. (2005) Drosera (Droseraceae). Flora Neotropica Monograph 96. The New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 65 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Correa &amp; 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[1394,1452,1238,1264]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
cite the specimen from P as the 
<typeStatus box="[583,685,1274,1300]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
. Even though the only specimen personally annotated by Taubert is the one held at B (thus representing the only suitable 
<typeStatus box="[737,844,1310,1336]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
), the citation of the specimen from K as an isotype by 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M." box="[136,404,1346,1372]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="75 - 105" refId="ref59136" refString="Silva, T. R. S. &amp; Giulietti, A. M. (1997) Levantamento das Droseraceae do Brasil. Boletim de Botanica da Universidade de Sao Paulo 16: 75 - 105." type="journal article" year="1997">
<taxonomicName authority="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann, 2022" authorityName="Gonella &amp; Sano &amp; Rivadavia &amp; Fleischmann" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,194,1346,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Silva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Silva</taxonomicName>
&amp; Giulietti (1997)
</bibRefCitation>
gives rise to an inadvertent lectotypification (ICN Arts. 7.11 and 9.10; 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1201,1420,1346,1372]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref59430" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) 2018: International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Glashutten: Koeltz Botanical Books. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[1296,1352,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[136,1452,266,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Natural hybrids with 
<taxonomicName authority="Rivadavia &amp; Gonella (2011: 34)" authorityName="Rivadavia &amp; Gonella" authorityPageNumber="34" authorityYear="2011" box="[437,986,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Droseraceae" genus="Drosera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quartzicola">
<emphasis box="[437,603,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">D. quartzicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rivadavia, F. &amp; Gonella, P. M." box="[612,986,1382,1408]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref57811" refString="Rivadavia, F. &amp; Gonella, P. M. (2011) Drosera quartzicola (Droseraceae), a new and threatened species from the Serra do Cipo, Brazil. Phytotaxa 29: 33 - 40. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 29.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Rivadavia &amp; Gonella (2011: 34)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were reported in the publication of that species, but photographs and specimens examined are first provided here (see ‘Natural Hybrids’ below).
</paragraph>
